         <OBJECT_CONTRACT>
            <TITLE>
               <P>Dynamic Purchasing Vehicle for SEN Provision</P>
            </TITLE>
            <CPV_MAIN>
               <CPV_CODE CODE="85000000"/>
            </CPV_MAIN>
            <TYPE_CONTRACT CTYPE="SERVICES"/>
            <SHORT_DESCR>
               <P>The London Borough of Brent in partnership with the West London Alliance (WLA) are establishing a 6 years (3 years + 1 + 1 + 1 years) Dynamic Procurement Vehicle (DPV) to procure and commission the provision of Special Educational Needs (SEN) schools and colleges services that are registered with the department for education.</P>
               <P>The estimated value of the services to be purchased for the entire duration of the DPV is purely an indicative figure.</P>
               <P>The DPV shall be divided into the following service levels:</P>
               <P>Day.</P>
               <P>— 38 Weeks residential,</P>
               <P>— 52 Weeks residential</P>
               <P>The DPV will be open to all London boroughs and any public body or local authority in England and Wales who are interested in joining the DPV. Access to the DPV will be gained through the signing of an access agreement with the London Borough of Brent.</P>
            </SHORT_DESCR>
