            <INFO_ADD>
               <P>This DPV will operate a selection and award process that is akin to a dynamic purchasing system as prescribed within Regulation 34 of the procurement Regulations 2015.</P>
               <P>The criteria for evaluation will be quality (“meeting the needs of the child /children”) and price with both quality and price criteria having a weighting range of between 90 % and 10 % depending on the individual authority’s priorities.</P>
               <P>Direct award call-off will be made using one or more of the following criteria: subject to the direct award procedures for emergencies and that fall within the scope of Regulation 32 of the procurement Regulations 2015.</P>
               <P>The criteria from which a unique provider or unique service requirement will be identified are as follows:</P>
               <P>— a child or young person’s view and /or parental preference,</P>
               <P>— compliance with decisions orders, judgements or directions from a SEN tribunal, and /or courts.</P>
               <P>This is a DPS procedure adapted under the light touch regime.</P>
               <P>Please got to https://wla.esourcingportal.com and download the procurement documents for more information.</P>
            </INFO_ADD>
